pros:
-It's fun to work with fresh graduates;
-You'll have plenty of time to do things you like;
-You will be given encouragement and guidance by experienced seniors and be practicing your research skills if your are interested in this field;
- The job is quite stable, at least for the junior ones;
- You do not have to work with other people, just focus on your own.

cons:
- It will be boring if you are really not interested in research;
- Payment is relatively low;
- Too free for me.
